---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Falck | How it feels"
  description="A calm workflow that lets non-technical teammates ship real code without the scary parts."
  theme="light"
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden pt-24 pb-20">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 backdrop-grid opacity-60"></div>
      <div class="absolute -top-20 left-[15%] h-[320px] w-[320px] rounded-full bg-emerald-300/40 blur-[140px] glow-pulse"></div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-[-25%] right-[5%] h-[420px] w-[420px] rounded-full bg-sky-300/40 blur-[160px] float-soft"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-6 reveal">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-white/70 px-4 py-2 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-600 border border-white/80">
          How it feels
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold text-slate-950">
          A workflow that respects the humans
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">
          Falck keeps the guardrails in place while you make real changes. You get a calm, guided path from idea to share,
          skipping the slide deck and the demo reel.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <Button href="/download">Download Falck</Button>
          <Button href="/features" variant="secondary">See the feature tour</Button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="surface p-6 reveal">
          <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-500 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">01</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Pick a goal</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Tell Falck what you want to change. It turns your idea into a plan.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface p-6 reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-2xl bg-slate-900 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">02</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Build with confidence</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Every step is explained. You never wonder if you broke something.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface p-6 reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-2xl bg-slate-800 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">03</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Save your progress</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Falck packages your updates so your team can look them over calmly.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="surface p-6 reveal-delay-3">
          <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-semibold">04</div>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold">Celebrate the merge</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Your work goes live. Your team gets the high-five and the clean history.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[1.05fr_0.95fr] items-center">
      <div class="space-y-4 reveal">
        <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-400">Why it works</p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold text-slate-950">Real contribution, no translation layer</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-600">
            Falck lets you ship what you mean. Your team can polish it later, but your intent shows up clearly and quickly.
          </p>
        <div class="grid gap-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-emerald-500"></span>
            You get a visual, guided workflow
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-emerald-500"></span>
            Teams keep their standards without extra meetings
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-emerald-500"></span>
            Everyone shares one clear source of truth
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="surface accent-card p-6 reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-400">
          <span>Falck in action</span>
          <span class="text-emerald-500">Shipping now</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-3">
          <div class="surface-muted px-4 py-3 text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold">Save queue</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">3 changes staged, ready to share</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-muted px-4 py-3 text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold">Version history</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-slate-500">Undo and retry without the drama</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-dark px-4 py-3 text-sm">
            <p class="font-semibold">Ready to share</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-emerald-100/70">Your team sees exactly what changed</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container mx-auto px-6 pb-28">
    <div class="surface p-10 md:p-12 text-center reveal">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-400">Ready to try it?</p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold text-slate-950">Invite your first non-technical collaborator</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Set up Falck once, and let everyone ship ideas that can actually go live. Bonus: fewer emergency Slack pings.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <Button href="/download">Go to downloads</Button>
        <Button href="/tech" variant="secondary">See the dev view</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
